description:
Implement Happy Coder's reducer pattern for client-side message processing.

**Reference:** ~/src/happy/sources/sync/reducer/reducer.ts (~1,150 lines)

**What It Does:**
Transforms raw messages into structured, UI-ready data while handling:
- Deduplication by message UUID
- Tool call lifecycle tracking (pending → running → completed → error)
- Matching tool results to tool calls
- Sidechain (subagent) processing
- Todo extraction from TodoWrite
- Usage data extraction

**Core Types:**
```typescript
export type ReducerState = {
    messageIds: Set<string>;                    // Deduplication
    toolIdToMessageId: Map<string, string>;     // Match results to calls
    messages: Map<string, ReducerMessage>;      // Processed messages
    sidechains: Map<string, ReducerMessage[]>;  // Nested conversations
    latestTodos?: { todos: Todo[], timestamp: number };
    latestUsage?: { inputTokens: number, outputTokens: number, contextSize: number };
};

export type ToolCall = {
    name: string;
    state: 'pending' | 'running' | 'completed' | 'error';
    input: any;
    result?: any;
    createdAt: number;
    startedAt: number | null;
    completedAt: number | null;
};
```

**Processing Phases (from Happy):**
1. Phase 0: Permission handling (future - for remote approval)
2. Phase 0.5: Message-to-event conversion (context resets, etc)
3. Phase 1: User and text messages (with deduplication)
4. Phase 2: Tool calls (create tool message, track ID)
5. Phase 3: Tool results (match to call, update state)
6. Phase 4: Sidechains (store nested messages separately)
7. Phase 5: Mode switch events

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// packages/web/lib/messageReducer.ts
export function createReducer(): ReducerState {
    return {
        messageIds: new Set(),
        toolIdToMessageId: new Map(),
        messages: new Map(),
        sidechains: new Map(),
    };
}

export function reducer(state: ReducerState, rawMessages: RawMessage[]): Message[] {
    const newMessages: Message[] = [];

    for (const raw of rawMessages) {
        // Deduplication
        if (raw.message_uuid && state.messageIds.has(raw.message_uuid)) continue;
        if (raw.message_uuid) state.messageIds.add(raw.message_uuid);

        // Process tool calls
        if (raw.tool_calls) {
            for (const call of raw.tool_calls) {
                const msg = createToolMessage(call, raw.timestamp);
                state.toolIdToMessageId.set(call.id, msg.id);
                state.messages.set(msg.id, msg);
                newMessages.push(msg);
            }
        }

        // Match tool results to tool calls
        if (raw.tool_results) {
            for (const result of raw.tool_results) {
                const msgId = state.toolIdToMessageId.get(result.tool_use_id);
                if (msgId) {
                    const msg = state.messages.get(msgId);
                    if (msg?.tool) {
                        msg.tool.state = result.is_error ? 'error' : 'completed';
                        msg.tool.result = result.content;
                        msg.tool.completedAt = raw.timestamp;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // Extract todos from TodoWrite
        if (raw.tool_calls?.some(c => c.name === 'TodoWrite')) {
            const todoCall = raw.tool_calls.find(c => c.name === 'TodoWrite');
            state.latestTodos = {
                todos: JSON.parse(todoCall.input).todos,
                timestamp: raw.timestamp,
            };
        }
    }

    return newMessages;
}
```

**Integration with Convex:**
Run reducer on messages from useQuery, store state in Zustand:
```typescript
function useProcessedMessages(conversationId: string) {
    const rawMessages = useQuery(api.conversations.getConversation, { id: conversationId });
    const [state] = useState(() => createReducer());

    const processed = useMemo(() => {
        if (\!rawMessages) return [];
        return reducer(state, rawMessages.messages);
    }, [rawMessages]);

    return { messages: processed, todos: state.latestTodos };
}
```

