Track and display token usage from agent messages.

**Reference:** Happy's latestUsage tracking in ~/src/happy/sources/sync/reducer/reducer.ts

**What It Does:**
Parse usage data from agent messages and display context consumption.

**Data Extraction:**
Agent messages may include usage info. Extract and track:
```typescript
interface UsageData {
    inputTokens: number;
    outputTokens: number;
    cacheCreation: number;
    cacheRead: number;
    contextSize: number;  // Total context used
    timestamp: number;
}

// In reducer, when processing messages with usage data:
if (message.usage) {
    state.latestUsage = {
        inputTokens: message.usage.input_tokens,
        outputTokens: message.usage.output_tokens,
        contextSize: message.usage.context_size || 0,
        timestamp: message.timestamp,
    };
}
```

