Port InvalidateSync pattern from Happy Coder (~/src/happy) to daemon file processing.

**What It Does:**
InvalidateSync is a smart synchronization primitive that manages data fetching with automatic retry and deduplication. From ~/src/happy/sources/utils/sync.ts:

```typescript
export class InvalidateSync {
    private _syncing = false;
    private _invalidatedDouble = false;
    private _queue: ((value: void) => void)[] = [];

    constructor(private fetcher: () => Promise<void>) {}

    invalidate() {
        if (this._syncing) {
            this._invalidatedDouble = true;  // Queue another sync after this one
            return;
        }
        this._syncing = true;
        this.#doSync();
    }

    async #doSync() {
        try {
            await backoff(this.fetcher);  // Exponential backoff on failure
        } finally {
            this._syncing = false;
            if (this._invalidatedDouble) {
                this._invalidatedDouble = false;
                this.invalidate();
            }
            this._queue.forEach(resolve => resolve());
            this._queue = [];
        }
    }

    awaitQueue(): Promise<void> {
        if (!this._syncing) return Promise.resolve();
        return new Promise(resolve => this._queue.push(resolve));
    }
}
```

**Why We Need It:**
Current daemon has ad-hoc debounce and retry. This pattern provides:
- Double-buffering: if invalidated while syncing, queues another sync after completion
- Backoff retry: exponential backoff on failures
- Promise coordination: multiple callers can await same sync via awaitQueue()
- Prevents thundering herd on rapid file changes

**Where To Apply:**
1. Session file processing (one InvalidateSync per file path)
2. Message syncing
3. Cursor position updates

**Usage Pattern:**
```typescript
const sessionSyncs = new Map<string, InvalidateSync>();

watcher.on('change', (filePath) => {
    let sync = sessionSyncs.get(filePath);
    if (!sync) {
        sync = new InvalidateSync(() => processSessionFile(filePath));
        sessionSyncs.set(filePath, sync);
    }
    sync.invalidate();  // Deduplicates rapid changes
});
```

